Checked Exception
1. All exceptions in Exception class excluding Runtime class throws checked exception.
2. Compiler force the users to handle the checked exceptions.
3. Example of checked exception - SQLException, ClassNotFound Exception etc.
4. To create user-defined checked exception, extend Exception class.
5. Throws keyword is mandatory while defining a func.

Unchecked Exception.
1. All exceptions in Runtime Class are unchecked exception.
2. Compiler does not forces users to handle Unchecked exception.
3. Example of unchecked exception - ArithmeticException, NullPointerException etc.
4. To create user-defined unchecked exception, extend Runtime class.
5. Throws keyword is not mandatory while defining a func.